4. Model Building:¶

In [30]:
def printPerformanceMeasurementParameter(model, X_train_p, y_train_p, X_test_p, y_test_p, y_class_Label_p, y_class_Pre_Label_p):
    model.fit(X_train_p, y_train_p)
    training_acc= model.score(X_train_p, y_train_p);
    testing_acc= model.score(X_test_p, y_test_p);
    
    if isinstance(model, KNeighborsClassifier) and len(y_class_Label_p)>2:
        testing_prob= model.predict_proba(X_test_p)
        auc = roc_auc_score(y_test_p, testing_prob, multi_class='ovr')
    else:
        testing_prob= model.predict_proba(X_test_p)[:,1]
        auc = roc_auc_score(y_test_p, testing_prob, )
    
    y_predict = model.predict(X_test_p)
    print("trainig accuracy", training_acc)
    print("testing accuracy", testing_acc)
    print("auc", auc)
    print("Classifier Report ")
    print(classification_report(y_test_p, y_predict));
    print("----------------------------------")
    print("Confusion matrix")
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_test_p, y_predict, labels=y_class_Label_p);
    df_cm = pd.DataFrame(cm, index = [i for i in y_class_Label_p],
                  columns = [i for i in y_class_Pre_Label_p])
    plt.figure(figsize = (7,5));
    sns.heatmap(df_cm, annot=True, fmt='g');
    return training_acc, testing_acc, y_predict, cm, auc

### Finding the value of best K value
In [40]:
N_neigbours = list(np.arange(3,50,2))
score = []
auc = []
misclassification = []
for n in N_neigbours:
    knn = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=n )
    knn.fit(X_train, y_train.values.ravel())
    score.append(knn.score(X_test, y_test))
    auc.append(roc_auc_score(y_test, knn.predict_proba(X_test), multi_class='ovr'))
    misclassification.append(np.mean(knn.predict(X_test) != y_test))

  
plt.plot(N_neigbours, score,'o-');
plt.xticks(N_neigbours);
plt.xlabel("Number of neigbors")
plt.ylabel("Accuracy")
plt.yticks(score);###
plt.grid()
plt.show()

#
plt.plot(N_neigbours, auc,'o-');
plt.xticks(N_neigbours);
plt.xlabel("Number of neigbors")
plt.ylabel("Auc Score")
plt.grid()
plt.show()

#
plt.plot(N_neigbours, misclassification,'o-');
plt.xticks(N_neigbours);
plt.xlabel("Number of neigbors")
plt.ylabel("Misclassification")
plt.grid()
plt.show()

Finding the Best value of K neigbors¶

In [80]:
N_neigbours = list(np.arange(3,30,2))
score = []
misclassification = []
for n in N_neigbours:
    knn = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=n)
    knn.fit(X_train_balance_sc, y_train_balance)
    sc = knn.score(X_test_balance_sc, y_test);
    score.append(sc)
    misclassification.append(1-sc)
plt.plot(N_neigbours, score);
plt.xticks(N_neigbours);
plt.xlabel("Number of neighbors")
plt.ylabel("Accuracy")
plt.show()
plt.plot(N_neigbours, misclassification);
plt.xticks(N_neigbours);
plt.xlabel("Number of neighbors")
plt.ylabel("misclassification")
plt.show()

According to the graph, we observed that K =3 is the best value in which Accuracy is high and misclassification is low.¶
